Suzlon May Get A$1.3 Billion Wind Farm Project, Australian Says

-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 
2011-08-30T15:30:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/suzlon-may-get-a-1-3-billion-wind-farm-project-australian-says.html
Suzlon Energy Ltd. (SUEL) ,  Asia ’s third-
largest maker of wind turbines, may win an order to supply and
develop a A$1.3 billion ($1.4 billion) wind farm in South
Australia, the Australian newspaper reported on its  website .  Suzlon plans to obtain approvals for the 600-megawatt
project requiring 180 turbines, the report said, citing Dan Hansen, head of Suzlon’s Australia unit. The Ceres project would
be located on South Australia’s Yorke Peninsula, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Obiko Pearson in Mumbai at 
 npearson7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
